Definitely. No CS major I know didn't take that class.

Another anon here: It's certainly an important class, but like everything it depends on you -- if you're planning on going EE or theoretical CS or something that isn't programming/systems heavy, then it's not necessarily vital for you to take the class (I know people who haven't). But for the 'typical' EECS/CS student it's pretty helpful.
Definitely. No CS major I know didn't take that class.

children.subject: Going on the student answer. 170/162 are both classes I feel everyone should take because I see them popping up everywhere in other uppder divs, and I only imagine even more so in industry. 188 expands on lots of the graph algorithms of 170. 186 uses the clock algorithm from 162, 168 expands on the brief survey of networking in 162. 162 is a lot of work sure, but I think its important work.

history.content: CS 170 is a class that is said by many is a class one should take if you're a CS major. I was wondering, is CS 162 also a class one should take if you're a CS major? Thanks!
